Great place for lunch in the nabe, lunch special is 9 bucks and their chicken shawarma is delicious and fresh. Pro tip, I found out by accident: if you get the shawarma/fries combo, let the stuff sit for at least 30 mins before eating. The grease from the shawarma will seep into the fries to delish effect. One Star off because they charge me extra for over a small amount of tahini and hot sauce. Cmon guys!

First time trying this place. I used it as lunch delivery.  I got the taboulah, tuna salad, and hummus lunch special. The hummus was excellent (be prepared it is a little bit spicy). Tuna salad was okay-ish I guess. The taboulah was very good as well. Only complaint is that the pita they gave me was tiny, like 5 inch diameter tiny. I also ordered rice pudding for dessert. This is really where the stars were lost. The rice was a bit undercooked and a couple pieces could be described as crunchy. It really would have been the winner cause the taste was pretty good but   the rice was definitely undercooked. So essentially, they have the classics down and some kinks to work out. Will give this place another try, maybe next time I'll do a proper sit-down.
